File: runtime/runtime-scopes.cc
Runtime slow paths and helpers for lookup-scope and with contexts:
- RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_PushWithContext) { NewWithContext(current, scope_info, extension_object); }
- RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_DeleteLookupSlot) { Context::Lookup(...); if in Context/Module: return false; else delete property on JSReceiver; }
- static MaybeHandle<Object> LoadLookupSlot(Isolate*, Handle<String> name, ShouldThrow, Handle<Object>* receiver_out): Core lookup algorithm walking Context::Lookup following chains; handles module exports/imports; context slots (incl. script context mutable heap number) with uninitialized checks; otherwise JSReceiver::GetProperty on context extension/with/global; returns undefined or throws ReferenceError depending on ShouldThrow.
- RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_LoadLookupSlot) { return LoadLookupSlot(isolate, name, kThrowOnError); }
- RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_LoadLookupSlotInsideTypeof) { return LoadLookupSlot(isolate, name, kDontThrow); }
- RUNTIME_FUNCTION_RETURN_PAIR(Runtime_LoadLookupSlotForCall) { returns pair {value, receiver} for call sites }
- RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_LoadLookupSlotForCall_Baseline) {...}
- static MaybeHandle<Object> StoreLookupSlot(Isolate*, Handle<Context> context, Handle<String> name, Handle<Object> value, LanguageMode, ContextLookupFlags=FOLLOW_CHAINS): Handles context slot writes (const errors, script context side data updates), module stores, or sets property on appropriate receiver (context extension/with/global), with strict vs sloppy behavior; sloppy-hoisting variant uses DONT_FOLLOW_CHAINS.
- RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_StoreLookupSlot_Sloppy|_Strict|_SloppyHoisting): Bind to StoreLookupSlot with appropriate mode/flags.
- RUNTIME_FUNCTION(Runtime_DeclareEvalVar/Function), Runtime_DeclareGlobals/DeclareModuleExports: related context/global declarations.
Also notable: feedback-related flags for script-context mutable heap number and const-tracking let flows; these tie into fast-path checks in Ignition and BGB.
